  <section id="page-info">
    <h3 id="headline">Here's a time line of Adams E. Hernandez's life:</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>2002</strong> - Born in Anaco, Venezuela.</li>
      <li>
        <strong>2012</strong> - Leaves his country to attend NCBIS "New Cairo British International School", where he learned English and his love for coding started to rise.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2014</strong> - He and his family left the country (Egypt) and moved to the United States of America where he continued his education and graduated from Freedom Middle School with multiple awards "top social studies student" and "top running athlete".
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2016</strong> - At only age 14 he becomes part of Rossy's Art & Crafts team who's founder is Rosiris Gonzalez (Adams's mother).
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2018</strong> - Adams creates the first website for Rossy's Art & Crafts where all of their current clients at the time would now have the access to their products, but online! Leading to a successful project.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2019</strong> - While Adams was working extremely hard and helping the company grow and expand, he also had the ambition to become a great runner and he for the first time qualified for AAU Nationals.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2020</strong> - Breaks school record for the Steeplechase event and right after this he also successfully created his first ever phone application using Swift, C & C#.
      
        He also received multiple certificionts;
        <br></br>
        <ul>Lean Six Sigma Black Belt Professional.</ul>
        <ul>Lean Six Sigma Green Belt Professional.</ul>
        <ul>Lean Six Sigma Yellow Belt Professional.</ul>
        <ul>Project Management Certified.</ul>
        <ul>Agile Leader Certified.</ul>
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>2021</strong> - Becomes a "Scrum Master Certified" and attends to WGU "Western Governors University" to get his B.S Business Management degree.
      </li>
    </ul>
